{"word":"φυτόν","slug":"φυτόν","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φυτόν</b></el> <el>(φῠτόν, οῦ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φύω'><el>φύω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>that which has grown, a plant, tree</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>generally <i>a creature</i>, of men, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>like <el>ἔρνος</el>, of men, <i>a descendant, child</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}